reviews.review_text:
Third
Show number three of four nights. This isn't the peak of the run, but it's summer '72 so it still has that sheen, sound, and high quality. Jer is still playing a Strat and Bobby is playing an ES-335. The 2nd set sequence is as solar as Aldebaran. First Set. Mostly GOGD, the set is played as standard run-throughs until Jack Straw, which has a faltered solo but also the first sparks. Me & My Uncle and Bird Song are strong, if stock. After Beat it on Down the Line-13, listen for Keith's Down by the Riverside/Bushel and a Peck tuning. Tennessee Jed is up there with top '72s. Playing in the Band doesn't match the best from the era, and brace yourself for Donnaskreech™. Casey Jones is enough to leave 'em happy for the break. Second Set. The quasar '72 shine arrives, starting with a souped Mississippi Half-Step. Listen to the interplay of Bobby, Keith, & Phil. Brown Eyed Women is perfect, if more sing-songy than GD. Truckin' is so, so tight; smooth through the verses and jams. This is a decent Dark Star, maybe as good as 8/21 and better than 8/27. Phil plays the Elastic Jazz riff @5:45, still incipient at this point. He plays it again @22mins, but now it's in ⅞ time. It occurs again in the fall [such as 11/17 in 6⁄8 & 13⁄8, and again 12/31 in ⅞ time – both in The Other One] and then emerges more developed in '73 in Dark Star, TOO, and even Truckin'. Things get pretty strange immediately after the verse, and there is lots of tugging while never completely losing momentum. Must hear once. Superb Morning Dew gets wild as fuck and then gets tamed as sin. The next few have some good, some flubbed, and you'll notice tape issues in Sing Me Back Home (scary Donna/good solo). The left channel is still crackly in One More Saturday. Uncle John's is a solid goodnight. 1st Set:  C+ 2nd Set: B Overall = 3½ stars Highlights: Tennessee Jed - that '72 sound Mississippi Half-Step Uptown Toodeloo - fabulous interplay Truckin' - both verse and jam sections Morning Dew - wild or tamed SOURCES: The 156469_sbd is an upgrade over miller_18093/unknown_151. It 's more dynamic, and fixes the switched channels and some levels and balance issues. It also restores tunings, however they are chopped into separate tracks, along with some song fadeouts.
